#100DaysOfCode – Day 1
Started learning Python today. Covered the basics and took the first step in my coding journey. Excited to keep learning and improving every day! 🚀🐍

#100DaysOfCode – Day 2
Today, I completed learning Python applications and explored how Python is used to build real-world solutions. This step helped me understand the practical importance of Python beyond basic syntax!.

#100DaysOfCode – Day 3
Today, I learned about inputs and outputs in Python and explored type casting concepts. I practiced taking user input, displaying output, and converting data between different types to understand how Python handles user interactions and data processing. Continuing to build a strong foundation, one day at a time.

#100DaysOfCode – Day 4
Today, I learned about variables and object references in Python. I also practiced practical examples such as swapping two variables and counting characters in a string. These exercises helped me strengthen my understanding of how Python stores and manages data while improving my problem-solving skills.

#100DaysOfCode – Day 5
Today, I learned about operators in Python, including arithmetic, comparison, logical, assignment, and other commonly used operators. I practiced using them in different examples to understand how they work and how they are used in problem-solving and decision-making.

#100DaysOfCode – Day 6
Today, I learned about Python keywords and different types of literals, including numeric, boolean, string, collection, and special literals. I explored their usage and gained a better understanding of how Python represents and handles different kinds of data.

#100DaysOfCode – Day 7
Today, I learned about data types in Python, including primitive and non-primitive data types. I explored their characteristics, usage, and how different data structures are used to store and manage information effectively in Python programs.
